	Please support Pegg by testing it and reporting bugs. !

------
New in 0.23:
- -w switch defines now the maximum printing width. If the label is smaller, the width
  will be adjusted. Contributed by Alex Perry

New in 0.22:
- Export to a pnm-file instead of printing a label. Contributed by Alex Perry
- Documentation rewritten
- Uninstallation target in makefile

New in 0.21:
- support for label sizes from 0px up to 2560px
- new commandline handler

New in 0.20a:
- test support for different lable sizes on KL-P1000 & KL-E11

Fixed in 0.16:
- Problems printing multiple times under some Linux Distributions

Fixed in 0.15:
- Makefile included
- some code enhancements inspired by M. Reising

New in 0.14a:
- printing support for KL-P1000
- better error handling

New in 0.13a:
- complete communication for KLP1000 label Printer (untested jet)

Fixed in 0.12a:

- Corrected output for pegg -t on a KLP1000 label Printer
- included a better test_raw
